at tool that \"),s(\"strong\",[e._v(\"helps web integrators keeping a consistent coding style\")]),e._v(\" in their (S)CSS files.\")]),e._v(\" \"),s(\"p\",[e._v(\"It applies a whole set of rules to our source code:\")]),e._v(\" \"),s(\"ul\",[s(\"li\",[e._v(\"indentation\")]),e._v(\" \"),s(\"li\",[e._v(\"spacing\")]),e._v(\" \"),s(\"li\",[e._v(\"properties ordering\")]),e._v(\" \"),s(\"li\",[e._v(\"syntax rules\")]),e._v(\" \"),s(\"li\",[e._v(\"etc.\")])]),e._v(\" \"),s(\"p\",[e._v(\"In our case, we always use SCSS so we will focus this guide on SCSS as the CSS content is compiled from our sources files in SCSS using Compass.\")]),e._v(\" \"),s(\"p\",[e._v(\"This is great news since we can (and must) provide a well formatted, well documented source code. We don't have to worry about the additional file size it represents... In the end, the compiled CSS code is compressed as much as possible to reduce its file size. And it is all automatic and painless.\")]),e._v(\" \"),s(\"p\",[e._v(\"Back in september 2014, we defined together the settings we should use when applying the big CSS Comb. The config file \"),s(\"a\",{attrs:{href:\"csscomb.json\"}},[s(\"code\",[e._v(\"csscomb.json\")]),e._v(\" is available\")]),e._v(\" and should be used with CSSComb since it respect as much as possible the syntax rules we chose.\")]),e._v(\" \"),s(\"h3\",{attrs:{id:\"_3-2-be-careful\"}},[s(\"a\",{staticClass:\"header-anchor\",attrs:{href:\"#_3-2-be-careful\"}},[e._v(\"#\")]),e._v(\" 3.2 Be careful\")]),e._v(\" \"),s(\"p\",[s(\"strong\",[e._v(\"Warning:\")]),e._v(\" as you may remember that with great power comes great responsibility.\")]),e._v(\" \"),s(\"p\",[e._v(\"CSSComb is no exception. While it can help, \"),s(\"strong\",[e._v(\"it can also harm the code\")]),e._v(\" you spent a lot of time to polish.\")]),e._v(\" \"),s(\"p\",[e._v(\"Here is my recommandation: \"),s(\"strong\",[e._v(\"isolate the usage of CSSComb\")]),e._v(\".\\nDo not apply CSSComb every time you change a SCSS fil